BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/kaufland.html"] = "<h3>Dairy alternatives</h3><ul><li>soya yogurt, soya milk, soya cooking cream (Alpro brand)</li><li>Soyatoo brand alternative to whipped cream</li><li>Alsan brand margarine</li></ul><h3>ice cream</h3><ul><li>Cristallo Big Choc Soya\" (lolly), 3x120 ml for €1.99</li><li>Swedish Glace Milkfree\" Magnum-style lolly</li><li>Swedish Glace\" chocolate or raspberry flavour, 750 ml for €2.59 </li><li>lemon sorbet in the zest of a lemon </li><li>raspberry smoothie-style ice lolly </li><li>Nimm2-Eis\" (ice pop with stick) </li><li>Nasch-Eisspezialitäten\" (vanilla or strawberry flavour)</li></ul>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/kuchenmafia.html"] = "The organic bakery Kuchenmafia is a bright and friendly corner café  located in the Neukölln district which opened only in June 2009. Here,  three vegan types of cake are on offer every day; additionally there is a  varying range of vegan cakes.<br/><br/>The cakes permanently on the menu are &quot;Linzer Torte&quot;, covered apple  cake and a super-yummy chocolate tart. Unlike the vegan breakfast you  can have as well, the vegan cakes are declared as such. So, when it  comes to the breakfast, you'd better ask explicitly for the vegan variant.<br/><br/>Allergy sufferers will be pleased to hear that soon they will be able  to buy gluten-free biscuits at this café. The rest of the menu is  exclusively organic-vegetarian. The drinks on offer include tea, coffee,  &quot;Bionade&quot; lemonade, etc., and you can have your coffee with soy milk.<br/><br/>Theres an extra playroom for children which, unfortunately, is also  the transit room to the lavatories. Nevertheless, it is a very nice  room, with a large table for the larger children and a smaller one for  the younger ones as well as a miniature shop, a rocking horse, etc.  There is also a changing table.<br/><br/>The toilets are not wheelchair-accessible, and handicapped people may  need assistance with the low step at the entrance. On inquiry, we were  informed that the owners are considering installing a ramp.<br/><br/>All in all, one can only recommend this café and its tasty food.<br/><br/>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/kurukshetra-vegetarischer-club.html"] = "";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/la-mano-verde.html"] = "La Mano Verde is a purely vegan gourmet restaurant. Accordingly, the prices are somewhat higher. <br/><br/>Go on a fascinating culinary expedition along the exciting menu in a cosy atmosphere. Even long-time vegans are amazed all over again by these interesting compositions. As a speciality, a number of the dishes are served as raw vegetarian food. <br/><br/>In 2009 La Mano Verde received PETAs Proggy Award granted to the best vegan restaurant.<br/><br/>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/lon-men.html"] = "";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/lush.html"] = "International Lush Fresh Handmade Cosmetics has 16 shops in Germany, four of which are located in Berlin.<br/><br/>Most of their products are vegan, and usually it is clearly stated on the packaging; however, if you are not sure about a product, the kind and competent shop assistants are always ready to assist you.<br/><br/>And all their products are cruelty free, innovative and made with natural ingredients and scents: from their famous \"baths bombs\" to shampoos, body lotions and soaps.<br/><br/>Lush is also well known for its involvement in Animal Rights activities. Therefore we always recomment Lush instead of the Body Shop, which is owned by L'Oréal.";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/majas-deli.html"] = "When it was opened, Majas Deli was the first completely vegan bistro in Berlin. It is owned by two nice vegan women who prepare all the food themselves with fresh ingedients. <br/><br/>They serve lasagne, gratins, soups, cakes, cookies, muffins, etc. The prices are OK. The range of dishes satisfies even demanding vegans. Even not yet vegans can experience that the cakes can easily match the taste of conventional cakes. All products also to take away.<br/><br/>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/manna.html"] = "Manna is a vegetarian café/restaurant in the Prenzlauer Berg district offering a daily changing menu of the day (as indicated on the information boards). It also has vegan meals on offer (these are internationally oriented: curry, pasta, lentil stew, and many more) as well as meals which can be adapted for vegans (e.g. the daily salad and the &quot;veggie burgers&quot;).<br/><br/>Mannas focus is on the seasonal vegetable cuisine. The ingredients are regional and mostly organic, and the prices are in the medium range. The portions are large and the waiters very friendly.<br/><br/>The home-made pastries on offer daily always include a vegan option (the plum scones are really great).<br/><br/>";
