BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/smart-deli.html"] = "Opened in 2002, Smart Deli is a small but noteworthy non vegetarian deli just a few metres from Boxhagener Platz. Several dishes are marked as vegan on the menu and the staff is usually well-informed.<br/><br/>The vegetarian sushi rolls/Maki are marked as vegan &amp;egg on the menu. Nearly all vegetarian options are suitable for vegans excluding, of course, the omelette sushi rolls (egg).<br/><br/>We recommend the sushi, tofu Teriyaki with rice, alga salad or miso soup. The prices are in the low range. Smart Deli also sells Asian foodstuffs.<br/><br/>Every Saturday there is an all-you-can-eat menu, the vegetarian variant of which is 12.50 and suitable for vegans as it does not include omelette Maki.<br/><br/>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/subway.html"] = "<h3>Sandwich</h3><ul><li>Veggie Delite without cheese</li><li>Barbecue Soße</li></ul><h3>Bread</h3><ul><li>Vollkornbrot</li><li>Sesam Brot</li><li>Italian Brot</li><li>Wraps</li></ul>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/supergood.html"] = "Supergood opened in the summer of 2009 and is located directly at the underground station Friedrichstraße. The first impression of this vegetarian restaurant is good: everything is clean and bright, the ambience is pleasant with lots of greenery and a small moss landscape.<br/><br/>Supergood has room for at least 50 people, the prices are okay and in line with those usually charged for organic dishes.<br/><br/>Although it is an organic-vegetarian restaurant, vegan dishes are not too abundant on the comprehensive menu. Max. 20&nbsp;% of the meals are declared as vegan. Unfortunately, none of the burgers and wraps on offer are vegan. The waiters are numerous and always friendly, however, often not too competent as far as veganism is concerned.<br/><br/>";
BVApp.models.Data["reviews/en/suriya-kanthi.html"] = "";
